## The Block System

Blocks are reusable components you can use in your EEx templates:

```elixir
# In your templates:
<%%= @block.(:hero, title: "Welcome") %>
<%%= @block.(:recent_posts, limit: 5) %>
<%%= @block.(:tag_cloud) %>
```

Sayfa ships with 15 built-in blocks including hero sections, navigation, table of contents, and more. You can also create custom blocks by implementing the `Sayfa.Behaviours.Block` behaviour.

## Customizing Your Site

### Configuration

Edit `config/config.exs` to set your site title, author, navigation, and social links.

### Overriding Layouts

To customize a layout, copy it for editing:

```bash
# List available layouts
mix sayfa.gen.layout --list

# Copy one to customize
mix sayfa.gen.layout post
```

This copies the layout to `themes/custom/layouts/` where you can edit it freely.

## Images

**Featured images** — Add `image:` to your front matter to display a cover image and set the OpenGraph image for social sharing:

```yaml
---
image: /images/cover.jpg
---
```

**Inline images** — Use standard Markdown:

```markdown
![Alt text](/images/screenshot.png)
```

Place your image files in `static/images/` and reference them with `/images/` paths.

## Multilingual Content

Sayfa supports directory-based multilingual sites. Place translations in language subdirectories:

```
content/
  posts/
    hello-world.md          # Default language
  tr/
    posts/
      hello-world.md        # Turkish translation
```

Generate multilingual content:

```bash
mix sayfa.gen.content post "Hello World" --lang=en,tr
```

In templates, use the translation function:

```elixir
<%%= @t.("recent_posts") %>
```

## Deployment

### GitHub Pages

Your project includes a GitHub Actions workflow. Enable GitHub Pages in your repo settings (set Source to **GitHub Actions**), and every push to `main` deploys automatically.

### Nixpacks (Railway / Coolify)

A `nixpacks.toml` is included. Connect your repo to [Railway](https://railway.app/) or [Coolify](https://coolify.io/) and select the **Nixpacks** build pack — no extra configuration needed.

### VPS

Build locally and sync:

```bash
mix sayfa.build
rsync -avz --delete dist/ user@server:/var/www/my-site/
```

